    Demo Case 05 - Resolved / General Inquiry / Medium priority
    ====================================================================

    Synthetic seed record for the case-management POC scoped application.
    This file is the FIFTH of the 10-case demo dataset; together with
    cases 01 through 04 and cases 06 through 10, it satisfies the AAP
    requirement (Section 0.7.4) of "at least 10 demo cases across all
    six statuses and both case types," and contributes to the dataset
    matrix:

        Case 01 - Draft       / General Inquiry
        Case 02 - Open        / General Inquiry
        Case 03 - In Progress / General Inquiry
        Case 04 - Pending     / General Inquiry
        Case 05 - Resolved    / General Inquiry / Medium      ## THIS FILE
        Case 06 - Closed      / General Inquiry
        Case 07 - Open        / Complaint
        Case 08 - In Progress / Complaint
        Case 09 - Resolved    / Complaint
        Case 10 - Closed      / Complaint

    The 10-case dataset thus exercises:
      * Every one of the six statuses (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending,
        Resolved, Closed) - this case occupies the Resolved slot for the
        General Inquiry case type
      * Both case types (General Inquiry and Complaint) across the
        full lifecycle - case 05 is the canonical RESOLVED GENERAL
        INQUIRY and is the General-Inquiry-flow analog of case 09
        (Resolved Complaint)
      * Multiple priorities (Low, Medium, High, Critical) - this case
        contributes to the Medium bar in the all_cases_by_priority chart

    Lifecycle position - WHY Resolved / General Inquiry / Medium is
    meaningful:
      A General Inquiry case that has reached Resolved status has
      traversed:
        Draft -> Open -> In Progress -> Resolved
      (skipping Pending; this case did NOT need to traverse Pending to
      reach Resolved). The agent has completed all investigative tasks
      and is now awaiting manager review for final closure. The Medium
      priority is appropriate at this lifecycle phase: the case carries
      moderate urgency through the investigation; with no Critical or
      High signal needed to escalate, Medium reflects routine handling
      that nonetheless completed the active-lifecycle phase.

