    Source-side semantic reference (read-only, NOT byte-for-byte ported)
    per AAP Section 0.8.1:
      acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/java/
        com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java
        ArkCase's CaseFile JPA entity declares ~80 fields including
        cm_case_status (the source for our <status>), cm_case_priority
        (the source for our <priority>), cm_case_type (the source for
        our <type>), cm_case_title (the source for our <subject>),
        cm_case_details (Lob; the source for our <description>), and
        cm_case_closed (Temporal TIMESTAMP; the source for our
        <closed_date>). The ServiceNow target collapses ArkCase's ~80
        fields to the user-prompt's 12-field schema (number, type,
        status, priority, subject, description, opened_date, closed_date,
        assigned_group, assigned_agent, requester_name, requester_email
        - plus the optional pending_reason). ArkCase's queue-handler-
        driven default status flow ("DRAFT" -> "ACTIVE" on save via
        CaseFileQueueHandler.java) is replaced in this POC by Flow
        Designer's general_inquiry_state_machine.xml; ArkCase's
        ChangeCaseFileStateService.java is replaced by the
        x_casemgmt_CaseTransitionValidator script include. ArkCase's
        CaseFileTasksService.java aggregation logic (which informed
        the "all tasks closed before resolve" guard) is replaced by
        the validate_resolved_transition subflow's inline GlideRecord
        query against x_casemgmt_case_task.

