    Key insights (per the agent prompt):
      1. Demo case 05 is the canonical Resolve-success case for the
         General Inquiry flow. It is the inverse of demo case 03
         (which is blocked because of an Open task). Case 05 has only
         Closed tasks, so the In Progress -> Resolved transition
         succeeds.
      2. THIS CASE IS THE RESOLVE-SUCCESS TEST. When the demo tasks
         are seeded, this case will have two Closed tasks ("Demo task
         04: Final review for resolution", "Demo task 05: Post-
         resolution archive"). The validate_resolved_transition
         subflow's GlideRecord query against x_casemgmt_case_task
         where case=current AND status!=Closed returns ZERO rows, so
         the transition is allowed.
      3. THIS CASE IS THE CLOSE-SUCCESS TEST. Subsequently, the demo
         manager (who has the case_manager role) can close this case
         via the form, demonstrating: (a) the validate_closed_transition
         subflow's role-check passes, (b) the set_closed_date business
         rule auto-populates closed_date. After closure, this case
         becomes one of the inputs to the avg_time_to_close widget.
      4. The status "Resolved" has a capital R. Not lowercase, not all
         caps. The exact choice value is "Resolved" per AAP Section
         0.5.7 and ../../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml.
      5. The <closed_date> field is intentionally empty. Even though
         this case is Resolved, it has not been Closed yet. The
         set_closed_date business rule is Before-Update on
         Resolved -> Closed, so the field is set only when the case
         actually transitions to Closed.
      6. Demo case 05 has both party types - Person (demo viewer as
         Requester) and Organization (Synthetic Org Beta as Respondent)
         - to exercise BOTH branches of the polymorphic UI Policy on
         the case_party form.
      7. The case appears in the case_count_by_status donut and
         all_cases_by_status bar in the Manager View dashboard's
         Resolved slice/bar.
      8. The case does NOT appear in the Agent Workspace's "My Open
         Cases" list. The list filter is "status NOT IN (Resolved,
         Closed) AND assigned_agent = javascript:gs.getUserID()".
         Resolved cases are excluded.
      9. Demo case 05 is the General-Inquiry-flow analog of demo case
         09 (Resolved Complaint). Both flows MUST behave identically
         when all child tasks are Closed; case 05 validates the
         general_inquiry flow's resolve-success path while case 09
         validates the complaint flow's resolve-success path.
     10. Medium priority is appropriate at this lifecycle phase: the
         case carries moderate urgency through the investigation and
         resolution; with no Critical or High signal needed, Medium
         reflects routine handling that nonetheless completed the
         active-lifecycle phase.
